# AI-S Project Constitution: Coding & Commenting Rules for AI Agents

You must follow these rules strictly when writing code or comments in this repository.

## 1. AI-First & Exception-Only Commenting Philosophy
- **Zero-Comment by Default:** Write clean, self-explanatory code with intuitive naming (variables, functions, classes) so that comments are **completely unnecessary**. AI agents analyze well-written clean code faster and more accurately without comment noise.
- **Exception-Only Comments:** Write comments **ONLY** in exceptional circumstances where the logical flow is non-standard or implements a critical workaround (e.g., RPC gas-fee check timeout fallback, Mock simulation mode triggers, API rate-limit bypass).
- **Single-Line Technical English:** When an exception applies, write only a single line of concise, structured, technical English explaining the *why* (the business constraint or workaround reason), not the *how* (what the code does).
- **No Redundancy:** Absolutely never comment on obvious operations (e.g., do not write comments for standard imports, variable declarations, or simple loops).

## 2. Strict Business Term Mapping
Always use consistent English terminology for core business concepts. Never mix or invent new terms:
- "매니저" / "메니져" -> `Manager`
- "본사" / "관리자" / "어드민" -> `Platform Owner` or `Admin`
- "정회원" -> `Active Member` or `Approved User`
- "배분" -> `Distribution`
- "가입비" / "입금" -> `Registration Fee` / `Deposit`
- "출금" / "인출" -> `Withdrawal`
- "그리드 봇" -> `Grid Bot`

## 3. Strict Coding Rules (Anti-Destruction)
- **Model Config Protection:** Never modify, overwrite, or delete `c:\home\alopop\config\ai_models.json` under any circumstances.
- **PM2 Safety:** Never run `pm2 delete all`.
- **Git Safety:** Never run `git add`, `git commit`, or `git push` automatically without explicit user permission.
